	abstract = {Experimental Synthesis of Fe 3 O 4 @mSiO 2 (R) nanoparticles Uniform 15 nm sized Fe 3 O 4 nanocrystals were synthesized using the previously reported method 39. The Fe 3 O 4 nanocrystals were stabilized with oleic acid and dispersed in chloroform with a concentration of 6.7 mg Fe/mL measured by inductively coupled plasma atomic emission spectroscopy (ICP-AES). 10 mg of rhodamine B isothiocyanate (RITC) was reacted with 44 μL of 3-aminopropyltriethoxysilane (APTES) (molar ratio of RITC:APTES = 1:10) in 0.75 mL of ethanol under dark conditions for 2 days. The prepared RITC-APTES stock solution was kept at 4 o C. In a typical procedure, 0.5 mL of the Fe 3 O 4 nanocrystals in chloroform was poured into 5 mL of 0.55M aqueous cethyltrimethylammonium bromide (CTAB) solution and the resulting solution was stirred vigorously for 30 min. The formation of an oil-in-water microemulsion resulted in a turbid brown solution. Then, the mixture was heated up to 60 o C and aged at that temperature for 10 min under stirring to evaporate the chloroform, resulting in a transparent black Fe 3 O 4 /CTAB solution. The resulting solution was added to a mixture of 45 mL of water and 0.3 mL of 2M NaOH solution and the mixture was heated up to 70 o C under stirring. Then, 0.5 mL of tetraethylorthosilicate (TEOS), 50 μL of RITC-APTES solution, and 3 mL of ethylacetate was added to the reaction solution in sequence. After 10 min, 50 μL of APTES was added and the solution was stirred for 3 h. The as-synthesized Fe 3 O 4 @mSiO 2 (R) NPs were washed 3 times with ethanol to remove the unreacted species and dispersed in 20 mL of ethanol. To extract CTAB from the NPs, 40 μL of HCl was added to the dispersion (pH {\textasciitilde} 1.4) and stirred for 3 h at 60 o C. To remove the Fe 3 O 4 cores as well as CTAB, 90 μL or more of HCl was used for extraction (pH {\textless} 1.0), resulting in hollow mesoporous silica (H-mSiO 2 (R)) NPs. After washing them twice with ethanol, the Fe 3 O 4 @mSiO 2 (R) NPs were redispersed in 10 mL of ethanol.},
